TY  - JOUR
AU  - Phelan, Christopher
AU  - Townsend, Robert M.
T1  - Computing Multi-Period, Information-Constrained Optima
PY  - 1991
Y1  - 1991/10/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297941
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 58
IS  - 5
SP  - 853
EP  - 881
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - This paper presents a detailed theoretical derivation and justification for methods used to compute solutions to a multi-period (including infinite-period), continuum-agent, unobservedeffort economy. Actual solutions are displayed illustrating cross-sectional variability in consumption and labour effort in the population at a point in time and variability for a typical individual over time. The optimal tradeoff between insurance and incentives is explored and the issue of excess variability is addressed by consideration of the analogue full-information economy and various restricted-contracting regimes.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297941
ER  - 



