TY  - JOUR
AU  - Chung, Tai-Yeong
T1  - Incomplete Contracts, Specific Investments, and Risk Sharing
PY  - 1991
Y1  - 1991/10/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297950
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 58
IS  - 5
SP  - 1031
EP  - 1042
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - An optimal contract design problem is considered. Contracts which are incomplete and simple are used to investigate the extent to which constrained revisions can mitigate inefficiencies resulting from contractual incompleteness. An optimal contract is characterized in two cases. First, when a contract is being used to facilitate trade between two risk-neutral parties who must make relationship-specific investments, it is possible to implement the first-best by a simple contract. Second, when a contract is being used to share risk, it is generally not possible to implement the first-best. When one party is risk neutral, however, it is possible to implement the first-best by assigning all the ex post decision rights to that party.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297950
ER  - 



