T1  - Employment Determination in British Industry: Investigations Using Micro-Data
PY  - 1991
Y1  - 1991/10/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297946
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 58
IS  - 5
SP  - 955
EP  - 969
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - This paper derives, and then estimates, a model of employment where unions and firms bargain over wages and possibly employment, and efficiency wage considerations may be important. It illustrates the difficulties associated in interpreting many existing attempts to discriminate between alternative models.The results (based on over 200 U.K. firms) suggest that employment is negatively related to the firm's own wage and the change in the own wage relative to outside opportunities. The latter may be an efficiency wage effect. Various financial factors are also seen to have a significant effect on employment.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297946
ER  - 



